 {"id":"bd-28jm","title":"Smart Resize Debouncing with Placeholder","description":"# Smart Resize Debouncing with Placeholder

## Background & Motivation

Terminal window resizing generates rapid-fire resize events. Rendering on every event causes:
- Excessive CPU usage
- Visual flickering
- Partial/torn frames

**The solution:**
- Debounce resize events with configurable delay
- Show lightweight placeholder during resize
- Apply final layout once stable

**Relationship to existing beads:**
- Requires bd-10i.8.1 (TerminalWriter) for resize event handling
- Enhances user experience during window manipulation

## Technical Design

```rust
pub struct ResizeDebouncer {
    debounce_ms: u32,
    last_resize: Instant,
    pending_size: Option<(u16, u16)>,
    last_size: (u16, u16),
}

pub enum ResizeAction {
    None,
    ShowPlaceholder,
    ApplyResize(u16, u16),
}

impl ResizeDebouncer {
    pub fn handle_resize(&mut self, width: u16, height: u16) -> ResizeAction {
        self.pending_size = Some((width, height));
        self.last_resize = Instant::now();
        ResizeAction::ShowPlaceholder
    }

    pub fn tick(&mut self) -> ResizeAction {
        if let Some(size) = self.pending_size {
            if self.last_resize.elapsed().as_millis() >= self.debounce_ms as u128 {
                self.pending_size = None;
                self.last_size = size;
                return ResizeAction::ApplyResize(size.0, size.1);
            }
        }
        ResizeAction::None
    }
}
```

## Logging Requirements

```rust
// Resize event received (DEBUG level)
tracing::debug!(width = width, height = height, "Resize event received, debouncing");

// Placeholder shown (DEBUG level)
tracing::debug!("Showing resize placeholder");

// Final size applied (INFO level)
tracing::info!(width = width, height = height, debounce_ms = elapsed, "Resize applied");
```

## E2E Tests

```bash
# Simulate rapid resize events
./ftui-harness --test-mode resize-stress --resize-count 50 --resize-interval-ms 10

# Assert: only 1-2 full layout computations
# Assert: placeholder visible during resize
# Assert: final size correct
# Assert: no visual glitches
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Debouncing works with configurable delay (default 100ms)
- [ ] Placeholder renders during resize (skeleton or message)
- [ ] Final size applied correctly
- [ ] No visual glitches during drag resize
- [ ] Low CPU usage during resize
- [ ] All tests pass","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-01T03:11:11.260468511Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-01T19:28:16.349902257Z","closed_at":"2026-02-01T19:28:16.349880105Z","close_reason":"Implemented resize debounce/placeholder in ftui-runtime","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-28jm","depends_on_id":"bd-10i.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-03T14:32:17Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-28jm","depends_on_id":"bd-10i.8.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-03T14:32:17Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
